{"article_id":"XLLfpO1VnT48H7Mu","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Republicans ' Obamacare repeal effort is on track to blow up","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"before it even gets started .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"The GOP is well short of the votes","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"needed","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"to bring its bill to the floor ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"and party leaders and President Donald Trump are kicking into overdrive","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"to save their imperiled health care overhaul .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"At least four Republican senators , Susan Collins of Maine , Rand Paul of Kentucky , Dean Heller of Nevada and Ron Johnson of Wisconsin , have signaled","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"they could oppose a key procedural vote","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that will occur either Tuesday afternoon or Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"A number of other senators , like Shelley Moore Capito of West Virginia and Marco Rubio of Florida , are undecided .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and his team are working furiously","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"to round up 50 of the caucus ' s 52 senators","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"to even bring the bill to the floor ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"let alone pass it by week ' s end .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"GOP leaders said ultimately","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"that even lawmakers","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"who oppose the bill in its current form","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"could be persuaded to allow the debate over the party ' s long-sought Obamacare rollback to begin .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"\" I would hope ...","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"our members would at least let us get on it , \"","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"said Sen. John Thune","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"( R-S.D . ) ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"the No . 3 GOP leader .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"\" Everybody wants to exert whatever leverage","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that they can ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"where they can get the most leverage ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"but I would expect","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"we ' d be able to get on the bill . \"","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"we ' re going to be in a good place , \"","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"added Senate Majority Whip John Cornyn","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"( R-Texas ) ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"the party ' s chief vote counter .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Sign up here for Huddle","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"A daily play-by-play of congressional news in your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"By signing up","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Simply overcoming the hurdle is becoming a massive headache for Republican leaders ,","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"and the Senate GOP seemed more divided than ever after the release on Monday of the Congressional Budget Office ' s analysis .","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"CBO estimated","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that 22 million more people will be uninsured over the next decade ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"but in good news for Republicans , the agency also gave them nearly $ 200 billion more","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"to spend on the legislation","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"to win over wavering senators with additional federal assistance .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Senators from Medicaid expansion states huddled on Monday evening ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"hoping to persuade McConnell to pour more money into Medicaid and opioid treatment ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"but budget hawks are eyeing an opportunity","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"to pocket the savings","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and decrease the deficit .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" We ' re trying to accommodate [ senators ' ] concerns","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"without losing other support , \"","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Cornyn said .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Trump and GOP leadership are doing all","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"they can","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"to tamp down criticism of the legislation and a voting timetable","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"that will provide perhaps just a couple of days","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"for senators to review the final product before a vote .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"But those efforts have been complicated by the Trump-linked super PAC America First Policies and its plans","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"to attack Heller and four conservative senators","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"for balking at the bill .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Sources close to McConnell said","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"they were concerned","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"the effort could backfire","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"and jeopardize the entire bill","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"by angering Heller , Johnson , Paul and Sens . Ted Cruz of Texas and Mike Lee of Utah .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"\" It ' s certainly not helpful , \"","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"said one of the sources .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"The second source called the effort \" buffoonish . \"","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"The party will meet in a full caucus lunch on Tuesday for a gut check","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"and some senators will dine with Vice President Mike Pence on Tuesday evening .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"In the interim , many senators refused to divulge their positions on the bill Monday","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"as the whip effort from McConnell and Cornyn stepped up","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"and the CBO score came down .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Sen. Joni Ernst","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"( R-Iowa ) ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"a conservative from a Medicaid expansion state , said simply :","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"\" I do have an opinion ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"but I ' m not going to share it . \"","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"McConnell worked on wavering senators by phone over the weekend ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Republican sources said ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"and Trump called undecided GOP senators","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"including Cruz , Johnson , Paul and Capito","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"to feel them out on health care ,","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"said White House press secretary Sean Spicer on Monday afternoon .","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Johnson said in an interview late Monday","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"that he made the argument to Trump","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that \" this bill doesn ' t do anything near enough","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"to address the price of premiums. \"","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"And the president ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"Johnson said ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"was \" sympathetic \" to his argument .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"\" I ' ve been very upfront with leadership for some time :","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"Don ' t jam us ,","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"don ' t jam the American public , \"","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"\" I have a hard time","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"believing","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"I ' m going to have the information","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"to vote for a motion to proceed . \"","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"The conservative Wisconsinite said","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"McConnell should delay the vote for two weeks","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"and also complained","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"that conservatives ' suggestions","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"to alter the bill in the Senate ' s working group","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"were mostly ignored .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Similarly , Paul said","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"McConnell and his team are doing little","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"to woo him .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"\" I had a long conversation with the president last night","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"and I think","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"he ' s open to negotiations ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"but we have not had any word from anyone in Senate leadership , \"","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"Paul said in an interview .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"The CBO score could complicate things further .","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"In addition to showing large coverage losses ,","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"including 15 million fewer insured next year ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"the agency projects","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"that the Senate bill ' s Medicaid changes would result in a 26 percent decline in spending on a program","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"that covers low-income Americans .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"Obamacare significantly expanded the program .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"\" I ' m not happy with the score , \"","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"said Heller , the most vulnerable Senate Republican in 2018 .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"CBO also projects","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"that insurance premiums would rise over the next year , a major problem for conservatives .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Powerless Senate Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"shut out of a process","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"that can circumvent filibusters ,","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"seized on the CBO report","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"to slam the bill .","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"The legislation amounts to a massive redistribution of wealth","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"that \" will force millions of Americans to spend more of their paychecks on health care","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"to receive fewer benefits","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"simply so the wealthiest Americans pay less in taxes , \"","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"said Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer of New York .","depth":5},{"id":141,"text":"Despite some calls by Republicans","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"to delay the vote into next month ,","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"most in GOP leadership believe","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"that letting the bill hang out over the Fourth of July recess will result in more \" no \" votes","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"and slow the GOP ' s momentum .","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"The president also suggested","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"that the party could let insurance markets collapse","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"if the bill fails this week .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"Republicans say","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"McConnell is ready for the vote to happen ,","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"even as they are uncertain about the prospects","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"- eager to move on from the issue one way or another .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"\" I ' m more nervous","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"than I was on Friday .","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"I still think","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"we can solve the problems","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"that a couple of members have brought up , \"","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"said Sen. David Perdue","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"( R-Ga. ) .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"Adding to the GOP ' s problems , the American Medical Association","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"- the nation ' s largest physicians professional group -","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"announced its opposition to the Republican bill Monday","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"because it would violate medicine ' s standard to \" first , do no harm . \"","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"Republicans did get one nod of approval .","depth":7},{"id":165,"text":"Insurance company Anthem said","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"the Senate bill \" will markedly improve the stability of the individual market and moderate premium increases \"","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"but acknowledged","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"the company is still reviewing the \" challenges","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"the current bill proposes \"","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"to Medicaid .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"Republicans released updated text on Monday","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"intended to promote continuous health coverage ,","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"which was left out of the discussion draft","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"released Thursday","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"and is designed","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"to encourage people to buy insurance ahead of an emergency .","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"An additional rewrite is expected shortly before the motion","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"to proceed to the bill ,","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"with additional horse-trading expected on the Senate floor , potentially in the form of amendments .","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"The revised Senate bill would include a six-month \" lock out \" period","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"in which people","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"who don ' t have insurance","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"have to wait","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"before their policy takes effect .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"The lock out would apply to people","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"who have been uninsured for at least 63 days ;","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"people would not have to pay their premiums during that time .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"The House bill would have allowed insurance companies to charge uninsured people up to 30 percent more for up to one year .","depth":9},{"id":189,"text":"Those provisions represent the GOP alternative to Obamacare ' s individual mandate ,","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"which is deeply unpopular","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"but helps keep insurance markets afloat .","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"Because Republicans are keeping the popular requirement","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"that insurance companies accept everyone","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"regardless of pre-existing conditions ,","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"which is expensive for insurance companies ,","depth":9},{"id":196,"text":"the GOP needs some policy","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"to encourage people to buy insurance .","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"Without it , insurance companies would experience a death spiral of too many costs","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"coming in","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"without enough healthy people on the rolls","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"to balance them out .","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"A White House official said","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"there will be big changes to the bill after the CBO score","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"which will determine","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"\" how much can be given to the moderates. \"","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"The Senate bill saves $ 188 billion more than the House bill ,","depth":6},{"id":207,"text":"which means McConnell has significant leeway","depth":7},{"id":208,"text":"to fund senators ' priorities .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":417,"left":252,"right":416,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":244,"right":251,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":210,"right":243,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":243,"left":224,"right":242,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":214,"right":223,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":214,"left":212,"right":213,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":212,"left":2,"right":211,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223